    "caption": "Diving from height with that enormous stretchy pouch ready to catch.",
    "shortDescription": "Pelicans have the biggest bill of any bird, and underneath it hangs a stretchy pouch that can hold three times more than their stomach. Brown pelicans dive from up to ten meters in the air, hitting the water headfirst to scoop up fish — and they evolved special air sacs under their skin to cushion the impact. Fun fact: A pelican's pouch can hold around eleven liters of water and fish at once."
